    <string name="recycler_lab_education_title">RecyclerView internals (sketch)</string>
    <string name="recycler_lab_education_body">Adapter: creates/binds ViewHolders; never do heavy I/O in onBind.\n\nLayoutManager: measures/layouts children; LinearLayoutManager prefetches ahead of scroll by default.\n\nRecycler + RecycledViewPool: detached views become scrap, then recycled by viewType; scrolling reuses without reinflating.\n\nDiffUtil / ListAdapter: computes minimal insert/remove/move so you avoid notifyDataSetChanged.\n\nThis screen measures frame spacing vs ~16.7ms (60 FPS) and ~33ms (30 FPS), and shows pool counts while you scroll.</string>

